{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":786,"text":"If I should have a daughter,"},{"time":3468,"text":"instead of \"Mom,\""},{"time":5603,"text":"she's going to call me \"Point B,\""},{"time":8928,"text":"because that way she knows\nthat no matter what happens,"},{"time":11579,"text":"at least she can always find\nher way to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14523,"text":"And I'm going to paint solar systems\non the backs of her hands"},{"time":17944,"text":"so she has to learn the entire universe"},{"time":19906,"text":"before she can say, \"Oh, I know that\nlike the back of my hand.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":23357,"text":"And she's going to learn"},{"time":25000,"text":"that this life will hit you\nhard in the face,"},{"time":28000,"text":"wait for you to get back up just\nso it can kick you in the stomach."},{"time":31319,"text":"But getting the wind knocked out of you"},{"time":33255,"text":"is the only way to remind your lungs"},{"time":35125,"text":"how much they like the taste of air."},{"time":37751,"text":"There is hurt, here,"},{"time":39300,"text":"that cannot be fixed\nby Band-Aids or poetry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41664,"text":"So the first time she realizes\nthat Wonder Woman isn't coming,"},{"time":45000,"text":"I'll make sure she knows"},{"time":46538,"text":"she doesn't have to wear\nthe cape all by herself,"},{"time":48961,"text":"because no matter how wide\nyou stretch your fingers,"},{"time":51475,"text":"your hands will always be too small"},{"time":53174,"text":"to catch all the pain you want to heal."},{"time":55715,"text":"Believe me, I've tried."},{"time":57718,"text":"\"And, baby,\" I'll tell her,"},{"time":59037,"text":"don't keep your nose up\nin the air like that."},{"time":61179,"text":"I know that trick;\nI've done it a million times."},{"time":63477,"text":"You're just smelling for smoke"},{"time":65000,"text":"so you can follow the trail\nback to a burning house,"},{"time":68000,"text":"so you can find the boy\nwho lost everything in the fire"},{"time":70643,"text":"to see if you can save him."},{"time":72573,"text":"Or else find the boy who lit\nthe fire in the first place,"},{"time":76000,"text":"to see if you can change him."},{"time":78501,"text":"But I know she will anyway,"},{"time":80000,"text":"so instead I'll always keep\nan extra supply"},{"time":82072,"text":"of chocolate and rain boots nearby,"},{"time":84214,"text":"because there is no heartbreak\nthat chocolate can't fix."},{"time":88158,"text":"Okay, there's a few\nthat chocolate can't fix."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90325,"text":"But that's what the rain boots are for,"},{"time":92587,"text":"because rain will wash away\neverything, if you let it."},{"time":96000,"text":"I want her to look at the world"},{"time":98000,"text":"through the underside\nof a glass-bottom boat,"},{"time":100606,"text":"to look through a microscope"},{"time":102000,"text":"at the galaxies that exist"},{"time":104000,"text":"on the pinpoint of a human mind,"},{"time":106199,"text":"because that's the way my mom taught me."},{"time":108231,"text":"That there'll be days like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110000,"text":"(Singing) There'll be days\nlike this, my momma said."},{"time":113000,"text":"When you open your hands to catch"},{"time":115000,"text":"and wind up with only\nblisters and bruises;"},{"time":117571,"text":"when you step out of the phone\nbooth and try to fly"},{"time":120000,"text":"and the very people you want to save"},{"time":121901,"text":"are the ones standing on your cape;"},{"time":123664,"text":"when your boots will fill with rain,"},{"time":125592,"text":"and you'll be up to your knees\nin disappointment."},{"time":128000,"text":"And those are the very days you have\nall the more reason to say thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131526,"text":"Because there's nothing more beautiful"},{"time":133405,"text":"than the way the ocean refuses\nto stop kissing the shoreline,"},{"time":136290,"text":"no matter how many times it's sent away."},{"time":138556,"text":"You will put the wind\nin win some, lose some."},{"time":142611,"text":"You will put the star\nin starting over, and over."},{"time":146000,"text":"And no matter how many land\nmines erupt in a minute,"},{"time":149000,"text":"be sure your mind lands"},{"time":150650,"text":"on the beauty of this\nfunny place called life."},{"time":153031,"text":"And yes, on a scale\nfrom one to over-trusting,"},{"time":155817,"text":"I am pretty damn naive."},{"time":158000,"text":"But I want her to know\nthat this world is made out of sugar."},{"time":161523,"text":"It can crumble so easily,"},{"time":163000,"text":"but don't be afraid to stick\nyour tongue out and taste it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166000,"text":"\"Baby,\" I'll tell her, \"remember,\nyour momma is a worrier,"},{"time":169000,"text":"and your poppa is a warrior,"},{"time":170858,"text":"and you are the girl\nwith small hands and big eyes"},{"time":173244,"text":"who never stops asking for more.\""},{"time":175000,"text":"Remember that good things come in threes"},{"time":177603,"text":"and so do bad things."},{"time":179508,"text":"Always apologize when\nyou've done something wrong,"},{"time":182412,"text":"but don't you ever apologize"},{"time":183817,"text":"for the way your eyes\nrefuse to stop shining."},{"time":186000,"text":"Your voice is small,\nbut don't ever stop singing."},{"time":189000,"text":"And when they finally hand you heartache,"},{"time":191000,"text":"when they slip war\nand hatred under your door"},{"time":194000,"text":"and offer you handouts on street-corners"},{"time":196000,"text":"of cynicism and defeat,"},{"time":198000,"text":"you tell them that they really\nought to meet your mother."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203570,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":204595,"text":"Thank you. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":211349,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212737,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":215000,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217033,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":220293,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221500,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":225000,"text":"All right, so I want you to take a moment,"},{"time":228000,"text":"and I want you to think of three things\nthat you know to be true."},{"time":232000,"text":"They can be about whatever you want --"},{"time":234000,"text":"technology, entertainment, design,"},{"time":236582,"text":"your family, what you had for breakfast."},{"time":238535,"text":"The only rule is don't think too hard."},{"time":241281,"text":"Okay, ready? Go."},{"time":249722,"text":"Okay."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251127,"text":"So here are three things\nI know to be true."},{"time":253358,"text":"I know that Jean-Luc Godard\nwas right when he said that,"},{"time":256413,"text":"\"A good story has a beginning,\na middle and an end,"},{"time":259461,"text":"although not necessarily in that order.\""},{"time":261772,"text":"I know that I'm incredibly nervous\nand excited to be up here,"},{"time":265000,"text":"which is greatly inhibiting\nmy ability to keep it cool."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268025,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":269382,"text":"And I know"},{"time":271000,"text":"that I have been waiting\nall week to tell this joke."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274336,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":275916,"text":"Why was the scarecrow invited to TED?"},{"time":278868,"text":"Because he was out standing in his field."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281765,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":284543,"text":"I'm sorry."},{"time":287265,"text":"Okay, so these are three things\nI know to be true."},{"time":290425,"text":"But there are plenty of things\nI have trouble understanding."},{"time":293632,"text":"So I write poems to figure things out."},{"time":297000,"text":"Sometimes the only way I know\nhow to work through something"},{"time":299834,"text":"is by writing a poem."},{"time":301311,"text":"Sometimes I get to the end of the poem,"},{"time":303233,"text":"look back and go,\n\"Oh, that's what this is all about,\""},{"time":305784,"text":"and sometimes I get to the end of the poem"},{"time":307825,"text":"and haven't solved anything,"},{"time":309184,"text":"but at least I have a new poem out of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311382,"text":"Spoken-word poetry is the art\nof performance poetry."},{"time":314105,"text":"I tell people it involves creating poetry"},{"time":316576,"text":"that doesn't just want to sit on paper,"},{"time":318488,"text":"that something about it\ndemands it be heard out loud"},{"time":321321,"text":"or witnessed in person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323249,"text":"When I was a freshman in high school,"},{"time":325178,"text":"I was a live wire of nervous hormones."},{"time":329542,"text":"And I was underdeveloped\nand over-excitable."},{"time":333000,"text":"And despite my fear"},{"time":335000,"text":"of ever being looked at for too long,"},{"time":337190,"text":"I was fascinated by the idea\nof spoken-word poetry."},{"time":340435,"text":"I felt that my two secret loves,\npoetry and theater,"},{"time":344099,"text":"had come together, had a baby,"},{"time":347052,"text":"a baby I needed to get to know."},{"time":348741,"text":"So I decided to give it a try."},{"time":350710,"text":"My first spoken-word poem,"},{"time":352638,"text":"packed with all the wisdom\nof a 14-year-old,"},{"time":356000,"text":"was about the injustice"},{"time":358000,"text":"of being seen as unfeminine."},{"time":360026,"text":"The poem was very indignant,"},{"time":362884,"text":"and mainly exaggerated,"},{"time":364050,"text":"but the only spoken-word poetry\nthat I had seen up until that point"},{"time":367302,"text":"was mainly indignant,"},{"time":369000,"text":"so I thought\nthat's what was expected of me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371358,"text":"The first time that I performed,"},{"time":373000,"text":"the audience of teenagers hooted\nand hollered their sympathy,"},{"time":376513,"text":"and when I came off the stage,\nI was shaking."},{"time":379000,"text":"I felt this tap on my shoulder,"},{"time":380911,"text":"and I turned around to see"},{"time":382491,"text":"this giant girl in a hoodie\nsweatshirt emerge from the crowd."},{"time":385426,"text":"She was maybe eight feet tall"},{"time":386865,"text":"and looked like she could\nbeat me up with one hand,"},{"time":389347,"text":"but instead she just nodded\nat me and said,"},{"time":392530,"text":"\"Hey, I really felt that. Thanks.\""},{"time":395514,"text":"And lightning struck."},{"time":396974,"text":"I was hooked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398471,"text":"I discovered this bar\non Manhattan's Lower East Side"},{"time":401763,"text":"that hosted a weekly poetry open Mic,"},{"time":404000,"text":"and my bewildered,\nbut supportive, parents took me"},{"time":407000,"text":"to soak in every ounce\nof spoken word that I could."},{"time":410000,"text":"I was the youngest by at least a decade,"},{"time":413000,"text":"but somehow the poets\nat the Bowery Poetry Club"},{"time":416000,"text":"didn't seem bothered\nby the 14-year-old wandering about."},{"time":419245,"text":"In fact, they welcomed me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420794,"text":"And it was here, listening to these poets\nshare their stories,"},{"time":423755,"text":"that I learned that spoken-word\npoetry didn't have to be indignant,"},{"time":426962,"text":"it could be fun or painful"},{"time":429306,"text":"or serious or silly."},{"time":431266,"text":"The Bowery Poetry Club became\nmy classroom and my home,"},{"time":434544,"text":"and the poets who performed"},{"time":436204,"text":"encouraged me to share my stories as well."},{"time":438608,"text":"Never mind the fact that I was 14."},{"time":440521,"text":"They told me, \"Write about being 14.\""},{"time":443640,"text":"So I did and stood amazed every week"},{"time":445743,"text":"when these brilliant, grown-up poets"},{"time":448000,"text":"laughed with me and groaned their sympathy"},{"time":450025,"text":"and clapped and told me,\n\"Hey, I really felt that too.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":454161,"text":"Now I can divide my spoken-word journey"},{"time":457427,"text":"into three steps."},{"time":459000,"text":"Step one was the moment I said,"},{"time":460841,"text":"\"I can. I can do this.\""},{"time":463000,"text":"And that was thanks to a girl in a hoodie."},{"time":465211,"text":"Step two was the moment I said,"},{"time":467290,"text":"\"I will. I will continue."},{"time":469482,"text":"I love spoken word. I will keep\ncoming back week after week.\""},{"time":472386,"text":"And step three began"},{"time":474000,"text":"when I realized I didn't have\nto write indignant poems,"},{"time":476824,"text":"if that's not what I was."},{"time":478246,"text":"There were things\nthat were specific to me,"},{"time":480435,"text":"and the more that I focused\non those things,"},{"time":483000,"text":"the weirder my poetry got,"},{"time":485000,"text":"but the more that it felt like mine."},{"time":487000,"text":"It's not just the adage\n\"Write what you know.\""},{"time":490722,"text":"It's about gathering up\nall of the knowledge and experience"},{"time":493571,"text":"you've collected up to now"},{"time":495206,"text":"to help you dive into the things\nyou don't know."},{"time":497969,"text":"I use poetry to help me work\nthrough what I don't understand,"},{"time":500876,"text":"but I show up to each new poem"},{"time":502845,"text":"with a backpack full\nof everywhere else that I've been."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506466,"text":"When I got to university,\nI met a fellow poet"},{"time":509215,"text":"who shared my belief in the magic\nof spoken-word poetry."},{"time":512731,"text":"And actually, Phil Kaye and I"},{"time":514749,"text":"coincidentally also share\nthe same last name."},{"time":517366,"text":"When I was in high school I had\ncreated Project V.O.I.C.E."},{"time":520125,"text":"as a way to encourage my friends\nto do spoken word with me."},{"time":523000,"text":"But Phil and I decided to reinvent\nProject V.O.I.C.E.,"},{"time":526000,"text":"this time changing the mission"},{"time":528000,"text":"to using spoken-word poetry\nas a way to entertain,"},{"time":531000,"text":"educate and inspire."},{"time":533000,"text":"We stayed full-time students,\nbut in between we traveled,"},{"time":535739,"text":"performing and teaching"},{"time":537591,"text":"nine-year-olds to MFA candidates,"},{"time":539999,"text":"from California to Indiana to India"},{"time":543369,"text":"to a public high school\njust up the street from campus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546000,"text":"And we saw over and over"},{"time":548001,"text":"the way that spoken-word poetry"},{"time":550000,"text":"cracks open locks."},{"time":552101,"text":"But it turns out sometimes,\npoetry can be really scary."},{"time":556823,"text":"Turns out sometimes,"},{"time":558339,"text":"you have to trick teenagers\ninto writing poetry."},{"time":561000,"text":"So I came up with lists.\nEveryone can write lists."},{"time":564489,"text":"And the first list that I assign"},{"time":566539,"text":"is \"10 Things I Know to be True.\""},{"time":569822,"text":"And here's what happens,\nyou would discover it too"},{"time":572202,"text":"if we all started sharing\nour lists out loud."},{"time":574345,"text":"At a certain point, you would realize\nthat someone has the exact same thing,"},{"time":579699,"text":"or one thing very similar,"},{"time":581700,"text":"to something on your list."},{"time":583000,"text":"And then someone else"},{"time":585000,"text":"has something the complete\nopposite of yours."},{"time":588000,"text":"Third, someone has something\nyou've never even heard of before."},{"time":591024,"text":"Fourth, someone has something\nyou thought you knew everything about,"},{"time":594493,"text":"but they're introducing\na new angle of looking at it."},{"time":597000,"text":"And I tell people that this is\nwhere great stories start from --"},{"time":600072,"text":"these four intersections"},{"time":602224,"text":"of what you're passionate about"},{"time":604000,"text":"and what others might be invested in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606407,"text":"And most people respond\nreally well to this exercise."},{"time":609676,"text":"But one of my students,\na freshman named Charlotte,"},{"time":612145,"text":"was not convinced."},{"time":614041,"text":"Charlotte was very good at writing lists,\nbut she refused to write any poems."},{"time":617691,"text":"\"Miss,\" she'd say,\n\"I'm just not interesting."},{"time":620003,"text":"I don't have anything interesting to say.\""},{"time":623111,"text":"So I assigned her list after list,"},{"time":625000,"text":"and one day I assigned the list"},{"time":626675,"text":"\"10 Things I Should Have Learned by Now.\""},{"time":629293,"text":"Number three on Charlotte's list was,"},{"time":631227,"text":"\"I should have learned\nnot to crush on guys"},{"time":633268,"text":"three times my age.\""},{"time":635695,"text":"I asked her what that meant,"},{"time":637092,"text":"and she said, \"Miss,\nit's kind of a long story.\""},{"time":639554,"text":"And I said, \"Charlotte, it sounds\npretty interesting to me.\""},{"time":642402,"text":"And so she wrote her first poem,"},{"time":644180,"text":"a love poem unlike any\nI had ever heard before."},{"time":647781,"text":"And the poem began,"},{"time":650226,"text":"\"Anderson Cooper is a gorgeous man.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":652368,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":654861,"text":"\"Did you see him on 60 Minutes,"},{"time":656502,"text":"racing Michael Phelps in a pool --"},{"time":658306,"text":"nothing but swim trunks on --"},{"time":660000,"text":"diving in the water, determined\nto beat this swimming champion?"},{"time":663156,"text":"After the race, he tossed\nhis wet, cloud-white hair"},{"time":665569,"text":"and said, 'You're a god.'"},{"time":666852,"text":"No, Anderson, you're the god.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":669000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":671000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":675000,"text":"Now, I know that the number one\nrule to being cool"},{"time":678816,"text":"is to seem unfazed,"},{"time":680727,"text":"to never admit that anything scares you"},{"time":683947,"text":"or impresses you or excites you."},{"time":685580,"text":"Somebody once told me"},{"time":687000,"text":"it's like walking through life like this."},{"time":689173,"text":"You protect yourself"},{"time":690571,"text":"from all the unexpected miseries\nor hurt that might show up."},{"time":693833,"text":"But I try to walk through life like this."},{"time":696487,"text":"And yes, that means catching\nall of those miseries and hurt,"},{"time":699378,"text":"but it also means\nthat when beautiful, amazing things"},{"time":703128,"text":"just fall out of the sky,"},{"time":704569,"text":"I'm ready to catch them."},{"time":706000,"text":"I use spoken word to help my students"},{"time":708405,"text":"rediscover wonder,"},{"time":710000,"text":"to fight their instincts\nto be cool and unfazed"},{"time":712790,"text":"and, instead, actively pursue being\nengaged with what goes on around them,"},{"time":716329,"text":"so that they can reinterpret\nand create something from it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719646,"text":"It's not that I think\nthat spoken-word poetry"},{"time":721963,"text":"is the ideal art form."},{"time":723463,"text":"I'm always trying to find\nthe best way to tell each story."},{"time":726622,"text":"I write musicals; I make short films\nalongside my poems."},{"time":729671,"text":"But I teach spoken-word poetry"},{"time":731869,"text":"because it's accessible."},{"time":733838,"text":"Not everyone can read music\nor owns a camera,"},{"time":737310,"text":"but everyone can communicate in some way,"},{"time":739699,"text":"and everyone has stories\nthat the rest of us can learn from."},{"time":743500,"text":"Plus, spoken-word poetry allows\nfor immediate connection."},{"time":746756,"text":"It's not uncommon\nto feel like you're alone"},{"time":748975,"text":"or that nobody understands you,"},{"time":750592,"text":"but spoken word teaches"},{"time":752000,"text":"that if you have the ability\nto express yourself"},{"time":754755,"text":"and the courage to present\nthose stories and opinions,"},{"time":757596,"text":"you could be rewarded"},{"time":759000,"text":"with a room full of your peers,"},{"time":761000,"text":"or your community, who will listen."},{"time":763310,"text":"And maybe even a giant girl in a hoodie"},{"time":765629,"text":"who will connect with what you've shared."},{"time":767699,"text":"And that is an amazing\nrealization to have,"},{"time":770000,"text":"especially when you're 14."},{"time":772466,"text":"Plus, now with YouTube,"},{"time":774000,"text":"that connection's not even limited\nto the room we're in."},{"time":776666,"text":"I'm so lucky that there's\nthis archive of performances"},{"time":779912,"text":"that I can share with my students."},{"time":781600,"text":"It allows for even more opportunities"},{"time":784069,"text":"for them to find a poet or a poem\nthat they connect to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":787867,"text":"Once you've figured this out,"},{"time":790358,"text":"it is tempting to keep\nwriting the same poem,"},{"time":792525,"text":"or keep telling the same story,\nover and over,"},{"time":794732,"text":"once you've figured out\nthat it will gain you applause."},{"time":797335,"text":"It's not enough to just teach\nthat you can express yourself."},{"time":800342,"text":"You have to grow and explore"},{"time":802000,"text":"and take risks and challenge yourself."},{"time":804321,"text":"And that is step three:"},{"time":807000,"text":"infusing the work you're doing"},{"time":809000,"text":"with the specific things\nthat make you you,"},{"time":811072,"text":"even while those things\nare always changing."},{"time":813709,"text":"Because step three never ends."},{"time":816549,"text":"But you don't get to start on step three,"},{"time":818577,"text":"until you take step one first:"},{"time":820765,"text":"\"I can.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":821802,"text":"I travel a lot while I'm teaching,"},{"time":823548,"text":"and I don't always get to watch\nall of my students reach their step three,"},{"time":827074,"text":"but I was very lucky with Charlotte,"},{"time":828816,"text":"that I got to watch her journey\nunfold the way it did."},{"time":831480,"text":"I watched her realize"},{"time":832836,"text":"that, by putting the things that she knows\nto be true into the work she's doing,"},{"time":836636,"text":"she can create poems\nthat only Charlotte can write,"},{"time":839100,"text":"about eyeballs and elevators\nand Dora the Explorer."},{"time":842412,"text":"And I'm trying to tell\nstories only I can tell --"},{"time":844777,"text":"like this story."},{"time":846000,"text":"I spent a lot of time thinking\nabout the best way to tell this story,"},{"time":849288,"text":"and I wondered if the best way"},{"time":850754,"text":"was going to be\na PowerPoint, a short film --"},{"time":852881,"text":"And where exactly was the beginning,\nthe middle or the end?"},{"time":855682,"text":"I wondered whether I'd get\nto the end of this talk"},{"time":858079,"text":"and finally have\nfigured it all out, or not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":861308,"text":"And I always thought that my beginning\nwas at the Bowery Poetry Club,"},{"time":864596,"text":"but it's possible\nthat it was much earlier."},{"time":866696,"text":"In preparing for TED,"},{"time":868000,"text":"I discovered this diary page\nin an old journal."},{"time":870263,"text":"I think December 54th\nwas probably supposed to be 24th."},{"time":874000,"text":"It's clear that when I was a child,"},{"time":876000,"text":"I definitely walked\nthrough life like this."},{"time":878277,"text":"I think that we all did."},{"time":880063,"text":"I would like to help others\nrediscover that wonder --"},{"time":883000,"text":"to want to engage with it,\nto want to learn,"},{"time":885489,"text":"to want to share what they've learned,"},{"time":887400,"text":"what they've figured out to be true"},{"time":889100,"text":"and what they're still figuring out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":891100,"text":"So I'd like to close with this poem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":894806,"text":"When they bombed Hiroshima,"},{"time":897411,"text":"the explosion formed a mini-supernova,"},{"time":900490,"text":"so every living animal, human or plant"},{"time":903568,"text":"that received direct contact\nwith the rays from that sun"},{"time":907270,"text":"was instantly turned to ash."},{"time":909152,"text":"And what was left\nof the city soon followed."},{"time":911265,"text":"The long-lasting damage\nof nuclear radiation"},{"time":913693,"text":"caused an entire city and its population"},{"time":916634,"text":"to turn into powder."},{"time":919146,"text":"When I was born, my mom says\nI looked around the whole hospital room"},{"time":922783,"text":"with a stare that said,\n\"This? I've done this before.\""},{"time":926424,"text":"She says I have old eyes."},{"time":928340,"text":"When my Grandpa Genji died,\nI was only five years old,"},{"time":931000,"text":"but I took my mom\nby the hand and told her,"},{"time":933173,"text":"\"Don't worry, he'll come back as a baby.\""},{"time":936284,"text":"And yet, for someone\nwho's apparently done this already,"},{"time":939472,"text":"I still haven't figured anything out yet."},{"time":942000,"text":"My knees still buckle\nevery time I get on a stage."},{"time":945000,"text":"My self-confidence can be measured out"},{"time":947000,"text":"in teaspoons mixed into my poetry,"},{"time":949000,"text":"and it still always\ntastes funny in my mouth."},{"time":952302,"text":"But in Hiroshima, some people\nwere wiped clean away,"},{"time":955547,"text":"leaving only a wristwatch or a diary page."},{"time":958325,"text":"So no matter that I have inhibitions\nto fill all my pockets,"},{"time":961781,"text":"I keep trying,"},{"time":963000,"text":"hoping that one day I'll write a poem"},{"time":965000,"text":"I can be proud to let sit\nin a museum exhibit"},{"time":967167,"text":"as the only proof I existed."},{"time":969855,"text":"My parents named me Sarah,\nwhich is a biblical name."},{"time":973000,"text":"In the original story, God told Sarah\nshe could do something impossible, and --"},{"time":977825,"text":"she laughed,"},{"time":979103,"text":"because the first Sarah,"},{"time":980704,"text":"she didn't know what to do\nwith impossible."},{"time":983072,"text":"And me?"},{"time":984456,"text":"Well, neither do I,"},{"time":986000,"text":"but I see the impossible every day."},{"time":988000,"text":"Impossible is trying\nto connect in this world,"},{"time":990929,"text":"trying to hold onto others while things\nare blowing up around you,"},{"time":994057,"text":"knowing that while you're speaking,"},{"time":995757,"text":"they aren't just waiting for their turn\nto talk -- they hear you."},{"time":998839,"text":"They feel exactly what you feel"},{"time":1000354,"text":"at the same time that you feel it."},{"time":1002000,"text":"It's what I strive for every time\nI open my mouth --"},{"time":1004501,"text":"that impossible connection."},{"time":1006605,"text":"There's this piece of wall in Hiroshima"},{"time":1009000,"text":"that was completely burnt\nblack by the radiation."},{"time":1011766,"text":"But on the front step,\na person who was sitting there"},{"time":1014464,"text":"blocked the rays from hitting the stone."},{"time":1016758,"text":"The only thing left now"},{"time":1018000,"text":"is a permanent shadow of positive light."},{"time":1020925,"text":"After the A-bomb,"},{"time":1022000,"text":"specialists said it would take 75 years"},{"time":1024612,"text":"for the radiation-damaged\nsoil of Hiroshima City"},{"time":1027000,"text":"to ever grow anything again."},{"time":1029000,"text":"But that spring, there were\nnew buds popping up from the earth."},{"time":1032389,"text":"When I meet you, in that moment,"},{"time":1034416,"text":"I'm no longer a part of your future."},{"time":1036276,"text":"I start quickly becoming\npart of your past."},{"time":1038539,"text":"But in that instant,\nI get to share your present."},{"time":1041000,"text":"And you, you get to share mine."},{"time":1043000,"text":"And that is the greatest present of all."},{"time":1045000,"text":"So if you tell me\nI can do the impossible --"},{"time":1047894,"text":"I'll probably laugh at you."},{"time":1049412,"text":"I don't know if I can change\nthe world yet,"},{"time":1051524,"text":"because I don't know that much about it --"},{"time":1053567,"text":"and I don't know that much\nabout reincarnation either,"},{"time":1056181,"text":"but if you make me laugh hard enough,"},{"time":1058049,"text":"sometimes I forget what century I'm in."},{"time":1060301,"text":"This isn't my first time here.\nThis isn't my last time here."},{"time":1063784,"text":"These aren't the last words I'll share."},{"time":1065720,"text":"But just in case, I'm trying my hardest"},{"time":1068000,"text":"to get it right this time around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1070896,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1072023,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1073877,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1074933,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1078190,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1079361,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1082222,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1083366,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}